  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Grate the ginger and garlic using the finest section on your grater. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop your coriander, mint, 1 chilli and spring onions. Then using a hand blender, blend it all together to create a paste and set aside (this is your green paste)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a separate pan heat a glug of oil. Chop your red onion and fry over a medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring regularly."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the onion becomes pink in colour add your grated ginger garlic paste and cook for 2 minutes. Then add the ground coriander and cook for a further 2 minutes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour in the yoghurt and simmer for 3 minutes giving it a good stir."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now, time to add the mince. Toss your mince, salt and bay leaves together and keep stirring until browned. Then, sprinkle over your flour and give it a good stir."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the green paste with a splash of water, mix and simmer for 20 minutes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your peas, 2 whole green chillies and leave to simmer for 15 minutes. Once this is done whack the lid on, turn off the heat and leave to sit for 10 minutes"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Whilst this is cooling, lightly toast your buns and chop your other red onion ready to serve."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the Keema is ready, split between 4 bowls and serve with a fresh wedge of lime, coriander leaves, chopped red onion, and your bread buns. Tuck in!"
    }
  ],
